hase 9: Forensic Metadata Centralization & Feature-Flag Registry
This phase focuses on eliminating hardcoded tag mappings and functional toggles across the parsing layer. By moving these into the GLOBAL_CONFIG registry, we establish a Single Source of Truth (SSOT) that allows for granular environment tuning (e.g., "Ultimate Mode" for deep forensic scans vs. "Lightweight" for rapid indexing).

User Review Required
IMPORTANT

Performance Impact: Centralizing feature flags allows the workstation to disable expensive operations (like chapter extraction or semantic validation) globally. This will significantly improve scan speeds for large libraries.

Registry Evolution: I will be creating a new structure within GLOBAL_CONFIG["parser_registry"] to hold these mappings. This is a non-breaking but significant refactor of the backend orchestration.

Proposed Changes
[Core] Registry & Orchestration
[MODIFY] 
config_master.py
Expand parser_registry with a feature_flags sub-dictionary.
Move all parser-specific tag mappings (VLC, Mutagen, ID3, EBML) into the registry.
Standardize forensic tag names (e.g., writing_app, muxing_app) across all parsers.
[MODIFY] 
media_parser.py
Refactor the orchestration loop to ingest feature_flags from GLOBAL_CONFIG.
Pass centralized tag maps to sub-parsers instead of relying on internal hardcoded dictionaries.
